        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(exec): add normalized auto mode",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds normalized `tools.exec.mode` support for host exec policy and maps `tools.exec.mode: \"auto\"` to Guardian-reviewed Codex app-server execution.\n\nThe native `auto` path uses deterministic allowlist/safe-bin matches directly. On approval misses, it asks the model-backed exec reviewer for a one-shot allow decision. Anything else routes to human approval.\n\n## Scope Boundary\n\nIncluded:\n\n- `tools.exec.mode` values: `deny`, `allowlist`, `ask`, `auto`, `full`.\n- Native gateway and node exec auto-review on approval misses.\n- Codex app-server mapping from OpenClaw `auto` to Guardian/`auto_review` approvals.\n- Plugin SDK subpath for exec approval policy helpers so the Codex plugin does not import core internals.\n- Docs/schema/baseline updates for the new config surface.\n\nNot included:\n\n- No session-persisted `execMode`.\n- No `execOverrides.mode`.\n- No slash `/exec mode=...` directive surface.\n- No auto-reply/session patch persistence changes.\n- No unrelated bug-fix backlog items.\n\n## Behavior Notes\n\n- If native auto-review returns `allow-once`, OpenClaw records and resolves a suppressed one-shot approval.\n- If native auto-review returns `ask`, malformed output, or anything unsupported, OpenClaw routes to human approval.\n- If auto-review asks for human approval, `askFallback=full` does not execute the command.\n- Bound native Codex conversation binding rejects touched exec policies that require interactive human approvals, because that path cannot route the approval back to a human.\n- Direct node `system.run` auto-review requires the prepared `systemRunPlan` before approved scoped execution.\n- Security-audit suppression edits stay on the human approval path in auto mode.\n- Sandboxed `exec` still works when global `tools.exec.mode: \"auto\"` is configured and `tools.exec.host` stays on the default `auto` route.\n- Legacy `security=full, ask=on-miss` stays full execution behavior; only `full/always` prompts.\n\n## Verification\n\n```text\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/codex/src/app-server/config.test.ts extensions/codex/src/app-server/run-attempt.test.ts extensions/codex/src/conversation-binding.test.ts src/agents/exec-auto-reviewer.test.ts src/infra/exec-auto-review.test.ts src/agents/exec-defaults.test.ts src/infra/exec-approvals-policy.test.ts src/agents/bash-tools.exec-host-gateway.test.ts src/agents/bash-tools.exec-host-node.test.ts src/agents/bash-tools.exec-host-shared.test.ts src/agents/bash-tools.exec.security-floor.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/approval-shared.test.ts src/node-host/invoke-system-run.test.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner.buildembeddedsandboxinfo.test.ts src/agents/pi-tools-agent-config.exec.test.ts\n```\n\nResult: 24 files passed, 690 tests passed.\n\n```text\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/codex/src/app-server/config.test.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner.buildembeddedsandboxinfo.test.ts src/infra/exec-approvals-policy.test.ts src/agents/exec-defaults.test.ts\n```\n\nResult: 6 files passed, 194 tests passed.\n\n```text\ngit diff --check\ngit diff --check origin/main...HEAD\npnpm docs:list\ncodex review --base origin/main\ncodex review --base origin/main\ncodex review --base origin/main\n```\n\nResult: whitespace checks passed, docs list passed, and three consecutive Codex reviews reported no actionable correctness issues on the final tree.\n\n## Real Behavior Proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Native OpenClaw `tools.exec.mode: \"auto\"` and Codex app-server Guardian-reviewed approvals now share one normalized config surface.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw source checkout on macOS with the focused Vitest suites above.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Ran the focused exec/Codex test command, the affected regression test command, both whitespace checks, `pnpm docs:list`, and three consecutive `codex review --base origin/main` passes.\n\nEvidence after fix: Focused suites passed with 24 files and 690 tests; affected regression tests passed with 6 files and 194 tests; final PR diff is 66 files, +5388/-491.\n\nObserved result after fix: Auto-review allow paths, auto-review-to-human paths, fallback-full blocking, sandbox exec with global auto mode, Codex app-server policy mapping, node `system.run` approval-plan enforcement, security-suppression human review, legacy `full/on-miss` reporting, and config/schema behavior are covered by passing tests.\n\nWhat was not tested: Live Codex app-server Guardian end-to-end approval flow.\n\n## Compatibility / Migration\n\nExisting `tools.exec.security` and `tools.exec.ask` continue to work. New configs should prefer `tools.exec.mode` for the normalized policy. Explicit lower-scope legacy policy values still take precedence where they already apply.\n",
